      "writtenOn": "2026-04-03T14:00:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good point. I\u0027ve initially only used a u32 hash based on the crc32c of the full path + len, but then decided to extend to u64 with path_len to reduce collision risk further, which in hindsight is not ideal.\n\nI\u0027ve implemented your suggestion to use clib_xxhash() directly, which iteratively hashes over the \u0027path_len\u0027 and \u0027path_indices\u0027 attributes of a path.",
      "parentUuid": "629f8d8e_b47f34a1",
      "revId": "878cd355eb9ca5c34127004d7cf3bb44a08b0632",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
